channel.title: Transformers 2 - More than meets the eye
channel.description:
So I saw the new movie considering the UK gets the movie 6 days before states >:} and I gotta say, this movie surpassed the first one in terms of comedy (watch out for 50 million sexual innuendos) and action.
You wouldn't believe how much stuff is going on screen at once, it was really hard to keep up, and if you blinked, you'd probably miss it, it was going that fast.
Now let me say this clearly, this wasn't a master class of a movie, it was a very damn good summer movie.
I'd recommend it for popcorn OMOMOM fun.
*Waits for Jambo's views of the movie as Australia gets it a day before the states*

item.title: Transformers 2 - More than meets the eye
item.dc:creator: John_Killer118
item.description:
I saw it at the drive-in last night.
It wasn’t terrible, but it just isn’t worth watching… at all. I’m sure kids under the age of 12 will love the film for its idiotic “comedy” and cool looking CGI. But to everyone else, it’s just an average action film.
Luckily, Star Trek played next, and the night suddenly went from shitty to fucking awesome! The best Star Trek film I’ve seen! The only problem is that Bones didn’t get enough screen time.
